However that did not stop the 24-year-old from saying a fond farewell to his former side.

'As I am about to enter a new chapter, I would like to thank AC Milan fans who have shown incredible loyalty and faith in me,' wrote Balotelli.

'I also want to thank the great staff who have shown exceptional patience and guidence over the years.

'Most importantly, I want to express endless gratitude to my team-mates who supported me on and off the pitch, just like my family does.

'Your camaraderie will be forever appreciated, as I've learned so much from you all. I leave Milan with sadness, but know that I will still make you all proud going forward. I'm forever grateful.'

Balotelli, who was forced into watching his new team-mates lose 3-1 to former side Manchester City at the Etihad Stadium on Monday night, will be in contention to make his Liverpool debut against Tottenham at White Hart Lane this weekend.

